						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga-chōḷadēva: Year 14 1st = 1163-64 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged in some places. It records the gift of one <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp to the deity Aviṉāśiyāṇḍār and an endowment of one <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> to provide for burning the lamp, by a certain Uyyavandāṉ Avināśi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Viratamiṭṭamālai, probably a <hi rend="italic">sāmanta</hi> (feudatory) of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
